06:53.137 --> 06:55.034
SO CHECK IT OUT.
HERE IS MY THINKING.

06:55.034 --> 06:57.103
THIS, TO ME, IS MORE
OF A CRUISER, YOU KNOW?

06:57.103 --> 06:58.965
THROW YOUR SURFBOARD IN,
YOUR SKATEBOARD, WHATEVER,

06:58.965 --> 07:02.310
BUT AT THE SAME TIME, I'M LIKE,
"IT NEEDS SOME ATTITUDE."

07:02.310 --> 07:04.551
-WE GOT A HELLCRATE UP THERE.
-YEAH.

07:04.551 --> 07:05.724
Richard:
SO WE GOT A HELLCAT MOTOR.

07:05.724 --> 07:06.896
YOU MAY ALREADY KNOW
THAT THE DODGE HELLCAT

07:06.896 --> 07:08.206
CAME OUT IN 2015

07:08.206 --> 07:10.793
WITH A 6.2-LITER
SUPERCHARGED HEMI ENGINE

07:10.793 --> 07:14.758
PACKED AT 707 HORSEPOWER,
MOST OF ANY MUSCLE CAR EVER.

07:14.758 --> 07:16.655
BUT WHAT YOU MAY NOT KNOW
IS THAT NOBODY'S PUT

07:16.655 --> 07:18.965
AN ACTUAL
HELLCAT MOTOR IN A SCOUT,

07:18.965 --> 07:21.620
AND THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I'M FIXING TO DO HERE.

07:21.620 --> 07:25.862
THIS IS GONNA BE DOWN,
DIRTY, FAST.

07:25.862 --> 07:28.137
LET'S PUT A NEW CHASSIS UNDER IT
TO HANDLE ALL THE POWER,

07:28.137 --> 07:31.413
TRICK OUT THAT CRAZY INTERIOR,
AND THE TOP, IT'S REMOVABLE,

07:31.413 --> 07:33.172
AND I DEFINITELY WANT
TO KEEP THAT.

07:33.172 --> 07:34.413
SO YOU'RE NOT GOING UP.

07:34.413 --> 07:35.517
YOU'RE GOING --
YOU WANT TO GO DOWN WITH THIS?

07:35.517 --> 07:36.931
I WANT TO GET RID
OF THE FOUR-WHEEL DRIVE,

07:36.931 --> 07:38.896
BIG MEAT IN THE BACK, OKAY?

07:38.896 --> 07:41.103
BIG, GET IT SQUISHED DOWN LOW.

07:41.103 --> 07:42.551
WHY? IT'S A SCOUT.

07:42.551 --> 07:44.448
IT SHOULD BE UP, OUTDOORSY,
FOUR-WHEEL DRIVE!

07:44.448 --> 07:46.793
LIKE THE SHART CAT MEETS
THE HI-PO HAULER.

07:46.793 --> 07:49.862
IT'S A CRUISER THAT HAPPENS
TO GO REALLY FAST.

07:49.862 --> 07:50.965
RIGHT.

07:50.965 --> 07:52.241
INTERNATIONAL CAME OUT
WITH THE SCOUT

07:52.241 --> 07:55.206
TO BE A FOUR-WHEEL-DRIVE
UTILITY VEHICLE.

07:55.206 --> 07:58.034
IT'S A MAN'S TRUCK,
EXCEPT IF YOU'RE RICHARD.

07:58.034 --> 08:00.068
NOW YOU'RE GONNA TURN IT
INTO A BOY'S TRUCK,

08:00.068 --> 08:02.241
SO I GUESS IT'LL NOW
BECOME A BOY SCOUT.

08:02.241 --> 08:04.172
BUT WHAT I LIKE ABOUT IT
IS THE KOOKINESS.

08:04.172 --> 08:06.724
I LIKE THE STRIPES,
AND I LIKE THE ORANGE,

08:06.724 --> 08:08.206
AND I LIKE THE PLAID INTERIOR.
-I DO, TOO.

08:08.206 --> 08:09.655
YOU WOULD WEAR STRIPES
AND PLAID TOGETHER.

08:09.655 --> 08:11.551
-I DO LIKE THE PLAID.
-YES, PLAID STAYS.

08:11.551 --> 08:14.172
MIKE! YOU'RE GONNA GET TO PAINT
SOMETHING ORANGE,

08:14.172 --> 08:15.793
NOT BLACK OR GREEN.
-WELL, I'M DOWN WITH THAT.

08:15.793 --> 08:19.724
I WANT TO HAVE WHAT I'M GOING
TO HAVE THE SCOUT II HELL

08:19.724 --> 08:21.000
BECAUSE IT'S A SCOUT II.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.172
WE HADN'T PAINTED
A LOT OF ORANGE,

08:22.172 --> 08:24.103
SO I'M FOR SURE DOWN
TO PAINT ORANGE.

08:24.103 --> 08:26.275
YOU WANT US -- DO YOU WANT
TO KEEP THE STRIPE PACKAGE?

08:26.275 --> 08:28.241
I WANT IT TO, AT A GLANCE,
EVERYBODY GO, "HOLY [BLEEP]!

08:28.241 --> 08:30.448
THAT'S, LIKE, A 1970 SCOUT,"
AND THEN LIKE,

08:30.448 --> 08:31.931
"WHAT IN THE HELL
DID THEY DO TO IT?"

08:31.931 --> 08:34.689
LOW CRUISER, GOT IT,
BUT SUPERFAST.

08:34.689 --> 08:35.758
YES.

08:35.758 --> 08:36.793
-GOT IT.
-LOT OF ATTITUDE.

08:36.793 --> 08:38.310
SO HOW MUCH TIME YOU GIVING US?

08:38.310 --> 08:39.413
CAN WE DO IT IN THREE WEEKS?

08:39.413 --> 08:41.034
OOH. YOU KNOW WHAT?

08:41.034 --> 08:42.793
I LIKE THAT THIS THING DOESN'T
LOOK LIKE IT'S HIDING ANYTHING.

08:42.793 --> 08:45.724
DON'T LOOK AT THE BACK CORNER.
DON'T COME BACK HERE AT ALL.

08:45.724 --> 08:47.206
THAT'LL BUFF OUT.

08:47.206 --> 08:49.241
YOU GONNA LEAVE THE ROOF RACK?
I THINK YOU LEAVE THE ROOF RACK.

08:49.241 --> 08:50.482
NO, WE'RE NOT LEAVING
THE ROOF RACK.

08:50.482 --> 08:54.620
WE'RE GONNA SMOOTH
THAT DOWN AND PAINT IT.

08:54.620 --> 08:56.758
HERE'S THE PLAN
FOR TURNING THIS 1979

08:56.758 --> 08:59.551
SCOUT II INTO
THE SCOUT II HELL.

08:59.551 --> 09:02.068
EVERYONE HAS SEEN THESE LIFTED
AND ROLLING ON BIG WHEELS,

09:02.068 --> 09:04.034
BUT WHAT'S THE MARKET
FOR ANOTHER ROCK CRAWLER?

09:04.034 --> 09:06.034
WE'RE GONNA GAS MONKEY
THIS ONE UP.

09:06.034 --> 09:08.068
WHEN THEY GO HIGH,
WE'RE GOING LOW TO SLAM THIS

09:08.068 --> 09:09.586
SCOUT TO THE GROUND.

09:09.586 --> 09:11.275
OF COURSE, THAT MEANS LOSING
THE FOUR-WHEEL DRIVE

09:11.275 --> 09:12.655
AND GOING WITH
ALL-NEW SUSPENSION

09:12.655 --> 09:14.862
AND A FORDLINK IN THE BACK.

09:14.862 --> 09:17.965
UP FRONT, WE'LL LOSE THE OLD V8
AND PACK IN A 707-HORSEPOWER

09:17.965 --> 09:19.689
HELLCRATE MOTOR.

09:19.689 --> 09:22.241
INSIDE, I'M LOSING THE BACK
SEATS BUT KEEPING THE PLAID.

09:22.241 --> 09:24.172
I MEAN, WHY NOT?

09:24.172 --> 09:26.551
AND OUTSIDE, JUST TO KEEP
THE WHAT-THE-HELL FACTOR,

09:26.551 --> 09:28.034
MIKE WILL LAY DOWN
A FRESH COAT OF ORANGE

09:28.034 --> 09:29.862
AND A NEW STRIPE PACKAGE.

09:29.862 --> 09:32.517
I WANT IT FAST.
I WANT IT LOW, BUT CRUISEABLE,

09:32.517 --> 09:34.034
AND I WANT IT DONE IN
THREE WEEKS,

09:34.034 --> 09:35.310
BUT I'M NOT HOLDING BACK
ON THE BUDGET

09:35.310 --> 09:38.724
BECAUSE THE GUYS ARE GETTING
75 GRAND TO GET IT DONE.

09:38.724 --> 09:41.379
THAT'S A TRUCK I COULD SELL FOR
MAYBE TWICE WHAT I PUT INTO IT.

09:41.379 --> 09:44.034
DAMN, I LIKE THAT.

09:44.034 --> 09:45.896
-BACK SEAT GOES AWAY.
-YEAH, THIS IS A TWO-SEAT.

09:45.896 --> 09:47.000
I LIKE WHERE YOUR HEAD IS AT,
JASON.

09:47.000 --> 09:48.827
AC COMES OUT
BECAUSE WE WANT POWER.

09:48.827 --> 09:50.103
THAT'S JUST TAKING AWAY
FROM THE POWER.

09:50.103 --> 09:51.793
-YOU JUST GIVE US THE CHECKBOOK.
-YEAH, WE GOT THIS.

09:51.793 --> 09:54.275
I ALREADY TOLD YOU,
75 GRAND AND THREE WEEKS.

09:54.275 --> 09:56.379
WE'RE GONNA TAKE IT INSIDE,
AND WE'RE GONNA GET STARTED.

09:56.379 --> 09:57.896
-ALL RIGHT?
-CAN YOU SAVE THE SEAT FABRIC?

09:57.896 --> 09:59.344
-I LIKE IT.
-RICHARD NEEDS NEW SOCKS.

09:59.344 --> 10:00.724
Richard: MAYBE YOU SHOULD START
PAYING ATTENTION

10:00.724 --> 10:02.310
TO WHAT WE DO AROUND HERE,
RUSSELL.

10:02.310 --> 10:04.137
AS LONG AS IT MAKES MONEY,
THAT'S GREAT,

10:04.137 --> 10:06.241
BUT TO BE ABLE TO GET IT
FROM THE HUNK OF JUNK

10:06.241 --> 10:08.344
THAT'S SITTING THERE NOW
TO THE HUNK OF JUNK

10:08.344 --> 10:11.344
IT'S GONNA BE AFTER
THREE WEEKS AND 75 GRAND,

10:11.344 --> 10:13.793
I GUESS RICH WILL HAVE TO PROVE
MY WRONG ON THIS ONE.

10:13.793 --> 10:16.310
WE BUILD, AND THEN WE SELL.

10:16.310 --> 10:18.827
OH. IT'S ORANGE.

10:18.827 --> 10:20.586
IT LOOKS LIKE A SAFETY CONE
ON WHEELS.

10:20.586 --> 10:27.000
♪♪

10:27.000 --> 10:28.379
WHOO!

10:28.379 --> 10:30.206
Narrator:
COMING UP ON "FAST N' LOUD"...

10:30.206 --> 10:31.689
WHY DO WE ALWAYS GET CRAP?
LOOK AT THAT.

10:31.689 --> 10:33.482
Narrator:
...RUST MIGHT BUST THE BUILD.

10:33.482 --> 10:34.689
THIS THING'S UNREAL.

10:34.689 --> 10:35.862
-AND...
-WHOO!

10:35.862 --> 10:37.172
-GET IT.
-ALL RIGHT, I'M GOING TO GET IT.

10:37.172 --> 10:39.275
Narrator: ...RICHARD GOES AFTER
A GAS MONKEY ICON.

10:39.275 --> 10:40.344
WHERE'S THE F40?

10:40.344 --> 10:43.034
THIS IS WHAT WE CAME FOR, B.

10:43.034 --> 10:45.206
[ LAUGHS ]

10:47.137 --> 10:51.448
♪♪

10:51.448 --> 10:54.379
WE REALLY SHOULD PUT A PLOW
ON THIS THING.

10:54.379 --> 10:57.137
THAT'S GOOD.

10:57.137 --> 10:59.000
WE NEED TO FIX THIS DOOR HANDLE.

10:59.000 --> 11:00.275
WELL, THAT'S ONE ON THE LIST.

11:00.275 --> 11:01.655
-YEAH.
-THIS ISN'T PERFECT.

11:01.655 --> 11:03.344
-I DIDN'T SAY THAT.
-WHY DO WE ALWAYS GET CRAP?

11:03.344 --> 11:04.724
LOOK, AT THE END OF THE DAY,

11:04.724 --> 11:06.793
EVERY ONE OF OUR VEHICLES,
THEY ALWAYS SELL.

11:06.793 --> 11:10.827
THEY MAY NOT ALWAYS MAKE MONEY,
BUT THEY ALWAYS SELL.

11:10.827 --> 11:12.551
TODAY WE TEAR DOWN
THE '79 SCOUT.

11:12.551 --> 11:15.068
RICHARD GAVE US A BUDGET
OF 75 GRAND

11:15.068 --> 11:18.206
BUT ONLY THREE WEEKS
TO GET IT DONE.

11:18.206 --> 11:19.655
I KNOW I'M THE PAINT GUY
AND ALL,

11:19.655 --> 11:21.068
BUT I'M NOT CONVINCED
THAT THE HELLCRATE MOTOR

11:21.068 --> 11:22.689
THAT RICHARD WANTS TO PUT
IN THIS THING

11:22.689 --> 11:24.275
ISN'T GONNA SNAP IT IN HALF.

11:24.275 --> 11:25.689
WHAT WAS THE OVERALL PLAN?

11:25.689 --> 11:29.068
-BIG MOTOR, LOW, FAST.
-YEAH.

11:29.068 --> 11:34.068
MY VISION WENT TO THE SHART CAT
MEETS THE HI-PO HAULER.

11:34.068 --> 11:35.689
THE SHART CAT WAS
A '67 DODGE DART

11:35.689 --> 11:37.758
THAT WE DROPPED
A HELLCAT MOTOR INTO,

11:37.758 --> 11:39.413
AND IT WAS FAST AS HELL.

11:39.413 --> 11:43.758
[ ENGINE REVS ]

11:43.758 --> 11:45.275
THE HI-PO HAULER WE MADE
FOR HOT WHEELS

11:45.275 --> 11:48.482
AND WAS OUR TAKE
ON A '60s-ERA DRAGSTER.

11:48.482 --> 11:49.931
I THINK HE'S ALREADY AGAINST
THE WALL IF HE GAVE US

11:49.931 --> 11:51.344
75 GRAND TO SPEND ON A SCOUT.

11:51.344 --> 11:53.172
AND YOU GUYS HAVEN'T EVEN
TAKEN IT APART.

11:53.172 --> 11:55.103
LET'S DO IT.

11:55.103 --> 11:57.000
Russell: I MAY NOT KNOW CARS
LIKE THE MONKEYS,

11:57.000 --> 11:59.689
BUT I DO KNOW I GOT TO KEEP THIS
THING ON TIME AND ON BUDGET,

11:59.689 --> 12:01.655
SO I KIND OF GOT TO HELP OUT.

12:01.655 --> 12:03.000
WHEW!

12:03.000 --> 12:04.758
OH. LOOK AT THAT.

12:04.758 --> 12:07.172
-WE GOT SMOKERS?
-WHEE!

12:07.172 --> 12:08.931
AND STILL NOT RUSTED.
USUALLY THAT MEANS...

12:08.931 --> 12:10.206
FOUND ITS HOME.

12:10.206 --> 12:11.862
-THE LEAVES SAVED IT.
-YEAH, RIGHT?

12:11.862 --> 12:13.827
SOMETHING SAVED IT.

12:13.827 --> 12:16.000
EVER HEAR THE SAYING
THAT SCOUTS WERE BORN RUSTY?

12:16.000 --> 12:17.344
HERE'S WHY.

12:17.344 --> 12:19.172
INTERNATIONAL HARVESTER BROUGHT
ROLLS OF CHEAP STEEL

12:19.172 --> 12:20.344
AND LEFT IT OUT IN THE RAIN.

12:20.344 --> 12:22.103
WHAT DO YOU GET WHEN YOU
MIX WATER WITH STEEL?

12:22.103 --> 12:24.172
YOU GET RUST AND THAT SAME
RUSTY STEEL

12:24.172 --> 12:27.931
THEY USED TO BUILD NEW SCOUTS,
BORN RUSTY.

12:27.931 --> 12:29.793
USUALLY THAT HOLDS THE MOISTURE
AND MAKES A BIG RUST HOLE.

12:29.793 --> 12:30.931
A SPOT LIKE THAT?

12:30.931 --> 12:32.275
OH, USUALLY THAT POCKET
IS ALL RUSTED UP.

12:32.275 --> 12:34.000
YEAH, LOOK AT IT. IT'S GREAT.
THIS THING IS UNREAL.

12:34.000 --> 12:35.551
OH, SOMEBODY'S HOME.
YOU CAN TELL SO...

12:35.551 --> 12:36.827
OH, DUST DAUBERS.

12:36.827 --> 12:38.379
THESE ARE THE KIND OF THINGS
WE LIKE TO DISCOVER.

12:38.379 --> 12:41.689
[ TOOL WHIRRING ]

12:41.689 --> 12:42.931
EH, DON'T GET TOO HAPPY.

12:42.931 --> 12:46.172
THIS IS WHERE
THE PROBLEMS START.

12:46.172 --> 12:47.620
OOH, HERE WE GO.
THERE'S SOMETHING.

12:47.620 --> 12:48.965
OH, MAN. THAT SUCKS.

12:48.965 --> 12:50.344
I FEEL LIKE THE BACK WINDOW
WAS OPEN OR SOMETHING

12:50.344 --> 12:53.172
AND IT GOT WET BACK HERE BECAUSE
THIS IS REALLY NOT TYPICAL.

12:53.172 --> 12:54.344
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

12:54.344 --> 12:55.620
LIKE, THIS SOAKED UP SOME WATER
OR SOMETHING.

12:55.620 --> 12:58.551
-HERE'S THE THING, THOUGH.
-YEAH.

12:58.551 --> 13:00.310
NOT MY JOB. I DON'T CARE.

13:00.310 --> 13:02.517
YOU WANT TO PULL THE BODY
FIRST AND THEN THE MOTOR?

13:02.517 --> 13:03.655
YEAH.

13:03.655 --> 13:05.034
THIS FRAME IS ACTUALLY
IN GREAT SHAPE.

13:05.034 --> 13:06.310
IF WE WEREN'T STRAPPING
A 700-PLUS-HORSEPOWER BEAST

13:06.310 --> 13:07.965
TO IT,
IT WOULD DO JUST FINE,

13:07.965 --> 13:09.310
BUT WE'LL
SAVE IT FOR ANOTHER BUILD.

13:09.310 --> 13:11.827
MEANWHILE, JEREMY WILL HIT UP
CHRIS ALSTON CHASSISWORKS

13:11.827 --> 13:13.896
FOR A SUPER FRAME THAT
CAN HANDLE THE HELLCRATE POWER.

13:13.896 --> 13:15.965
WE MADE AN ABSOLUTE DISASTER.

13:15.965 --> 13:21.206
♪♪

13:21.206 --> 13:24.310
Richard: WE'RE IN AN UNDISCLOSED
LOCATION HERE IN CALIFORNIA.

13:24.310 --> 13:27.827
THE F40 THAT GAS MONKEY BUILT,
WHICH WAS AN AMAZING CAR,

13:27.827 --> 13:29.034
HAS FOUND ITS WAY INTO

13:29.034 --> 13:30.793
A NOT-SO-AMAZING GUY'S
POSSESSION,

13:30.793 --> 13:33.724
AND THE GOVERNMENT
TOOK IT FROM HIM.

13:33.724 --> 13:35.034
I REALLY HUNG IT
ALL OUT THERE ON THE LINE

13:35.034 --> 13:37.344
WHEN WE BOUGHT A WRECKED
FERRARI F40 FOR 400 GRAND

13:37.344 --> 13:45.827
AND BUILT IT INTO A BETTER CAR
THAN IT WAS NEW.

13:45.827 --> 13:47.000
HALL OF FAMER REGGIE JACKSON

13:47.000 --> 13:50.793
PAID 650 GRAND FOR IT
AT AUCTION.

13:50.793 --> 13:54.344
A YEAR LATER, HE TOOK A LOSS
WHEN HE SOLD IT FOR $590,000.

13:54.344 --> 13:56.517
-HE'S FIXING TO LOSE 110 GRAND.
-YEP.

13:56.517 --> 13:58.068
Auctioneer: SOLD!

13:58.068 --> 13:59.103
Richard: NOW, I'M TOLD
IT'S CHANGED HANDS AGAIN,

13:59.103 --> 14:00.551
AND THEN THE NEW OWNER,

14:00.551 --> 14:03.137
HE'S ACCUSED OF RIPPING OFF
THE V.A. FOR $11 MILLION,

14:03.137 --> 14:06.000
AND THE U.S. MARSHALS
SEIZED HIS CARS.

14:06.000 --> 14:08.206
AND I GRABBED DENNIS
AND RUSSELL AND HERE WE ARE.

14:08.206 --> 14:10.896
WE'RE GONNA TAKE A LOOK AT IT
BECAUSE IF WE CAN BUY IT AGAIN

14:10.896 --> 14:13.310
AND MAKE SOME MONEY, WELL,
THAT'S WHAT GAS MONKEY DOES.

14:13.310 --> 14:14.827
-ARE YOU GOOD? WHOO!
-GET IT.

14:14.827 --> 14:16.103
ALL RIGHT.
I'M GOING TO GET IT.

14:16.103 --> 14:18.689
COME ON, MEN. HERE WE GO.

14:18.689 --> 14:22.655
♪♪

14:22.655 --> 14:25.827
WOW. THAT GUY
HAD GOOD TASTE IN CARS.

14:25.827 --> 14:26.862
Richard: OPEN THE DOOR

14:26.862 --> 14:28.034
AND THERE'S TONS OF CARS
IN THERE.

14:28.034 --> 14:29.758
THERE'S LOWRIDERS.
THERE'S OTHER FERRARIS.

14:29.758 --> 14:32.689
THERE'S CORVETTES, AND I'M
LIKE A KID IN A CANDY STORE.

14:32.689 --> 14:34.000
I MEAN, THIS IS --

14:34.000 --> 14:35.310
THIS COULD BE A LOT OF CARS
WE COULD BUY CHEAP.

14:35.310 --> 14:37.068
THAT'S A GOOD-LOOKING CAR.
HOW YOU DOING, GUYS?

14:37.068 --> 14:38.172
-RICHARD RAWLINGS.
-MIKE SCULLEY.

14:38.172 --> 14:39.379
NICE TO MEET YOU, BROTHER.
WELCOME.

14:39.379 --> 14:41.172
-DENNIS COLLINS.
-MIKE PENNINGTON, U.S. MARSHALS.

14:41.172 --> 14:42.517
OH, YOU'RE THE U.S. MARSHAL.

14:42.517 --> 14:43.862
-YES, SIR.
-ABSOLUTELY.

14:43.862 --> 14:45.586
HE CAN KEEP YOU IN LINE.

14:45.586 --> 14:47.655
MY NAME IS MIKE PENNINGTON,
DEPUTY U.S. MARSHAL.

14:47.655 --> 14:49.448
WE'VE HAD OUR RUN-INS.

14:49.448 --> 14:52.206
I'M PRETTY SURE OUR BACKGROUNDS
HAVE BEEN THOROUGHLY CHECKED.

14:52.206 --> 14:54.206
I'M KNOWN IN THE BUSINESS
AS A GUN-TOTER.

14:54.206 --> 14:57.551
WE HUNT FUGITIVES AND SOMETIMES
DO THINGS LIKE THIS.

14:57.551 --> 15:00.137
WERE ALL OF THESE
AT THIS GUY'S COLLECTION OR...

15:00.137 --> 15:01.827
HE'S GOT ABOUT EIGHT
OR NINE OF THEM.

15:01.827 --> 15:03.620
WE'VE GOT A '69 CORVETTE

15:03.620 --> 15:06.068
WE BELIEVE IS TO BE
AN L88 SERIES,

15:06.068 --> 15:08.793
POSSIBLY BEING ONE OF TWO
LEFT IN EXISTENCE.

15:08.793 --> 15:10.310
IT COULD BE HOLY GRAIL.

15:10.310 --> 15:13.689
THIS CAME FORM THE INDIVIDUAL,
THE SAME AS THE FERRARI.

15:13.689 --> 15:15.206
WHAT MAKES THIS CAR SPECIAL?

15:15.206 --> 15:17.172
ALUMINUM HEADS, IT'S THE BIGGEST
HORSEPOWER THEY EVER BUILT.

15:17.172 --> 15:20.586
-TRIPLE BLACK.
-THIS IS A KILLER CAR.

15:20.586 --> 15:22.034
-IT'S A MONSTER.
-IT'S SLICK.

15:22.034 --> 15:24.482
WHEN THESE GO FOR AUCTION,
WHERE DO THE PROCEEDS GO?

15:24.482 --> 15:25.551
-RESTITUTION --
-OKAY.

15:25.551 --> 15:27.206
-...FOR THE VICTIMS.
-SURE.

15:27.206 --> 15:29.103
YEAH, THE LEFTOVERS
GO TO THE FORFEITURE FUND,

15:29.103 --> 15:32.206
AND THAT FORFEITURE FUND
IS USED TO FIGHT CRIME.

15:32.206 --> 15:34.965
-WHERE'S THE F40?
-IT'S OVER HERE, MAN.

15:34.965 --> 15:38.310
-THIS IS WHAT WE CAME FOR, D.
-[ WHISTLES ]

15:38.310 --> 15:42.068
-HAVE YOU EVER SEEN THIS CAR?
-ONLY ON TV.

15:42.068 --> 15:45.103
PROBABLY THE HARDEST BUILD
THAT WE EVER DID.

15:45.103 --> 15:46.448
GET YOU SOME OF THIS, CHIEF.

15:46.448 --> 15:48.068
HOLY [BLEEP].

15:48.068 --> 15:49.827
THAT'S AN F40, DUDE.

15:49.827 --> 15:53.206
WE PICKED UP THIS SORRY WRECK
OF A FERRARI F40 FOR 400 GRAND

15:53.206 --> 15:55.931
AFTER A MECHANIC T-BONED
A BUILDING ON A TEST DRIVE.

15:55.931 --> 15:59.551
SO THE OWNER OF THE CAR
DIDN'T WRECK IT?

15:59.551 --> 16:01.379
[ LAUGHS ] HOLY COW.

16:01.379 --> 16:04.172
WHEN WE GOT AFTER IT, THE F40
HAD TO COME OUT BETTER THAN NEW,

16:04.172 --> 16:05.448
AND THAT WOULDN'T COME CHEAP.

16:05.448 --> 16:07.413
MOST OF THOSE PARTS
HAD TO BE IMPORTED.

16:07.413 --> 16:09.344
DO YOU HAVE ANY MOVEMENT
ON YOUR PRICE?

16:09.344 --> 16:10.758
[ GROANS ]

16:10.758 --> 16:11.965
WE DID MAJOR SURGERY
ON THE FRAME

16:11.965 --> 16:13.724
AND REPLACED
PRACTICALLY THE ENTIRE BODY

16:13.724 --> 16:16.034
AND, OH, BY THE WAY,
MADE IT LIGHTER,

16:16.034 --> 16:18.586
FASTER, BETTER HANDLING,
AND GAVE THE FERRARI PURISTS

16:18.586 --> 16:22.448
THE MIDDLE FINGER
BY PAINTING IT BLACK.

16:22.448 --> 16:24.724
AND SINCE
WE PAINTED THIS BLACK,

16:24.724 --> 16:26.620
THERE'S BEEN AT LEAST
FOUR OTHERS

16:26.620 --> 16:28.172
THAT I KNOW OF THAT
PEOPLE HAVE PAINTED BLACK.

16:28.172 --> 16:31.103
YEAH, THIS WAS IT, DEFINITELY.
IT WAS A MAJOR NO-NO.

16:31.103 --> 16:33.689
EVERYBODY WAS SCARED TO DO THAT,
AND WE DID IT.

16:33.689 --> 16:35.620
-WE BUILT A BETTER F40.
-YEAH.

16:35.620 --> 16:36.965
AND THAT'S WHAT GAS MONKEY DOES.

16:36.965 --> 16:40.068
WE DO BETTER THAN FERRARI.

16:40.068 --> 16:41.344
OOF, THAT SHOULD BE
A BUMPER STICKER.

16:41.344 --> 16:42.965
"GAS MONKEY:
BETTER THAN FERRARI."

16:42.965 --> 16:44.586
[ LAUGHS ]

16:44.586 --> 16:46.586
BEFORE WE GET BACK
TO THE AIRPORT,

16:46.586 --> 16:49.793
WE'RE GONNA GIVE YOU THE LIST
OF THE CARS THAT WE'VE LOOKED AT

16:49.793 --> 16:51.068
AND WHAT WE'RE WILLING TO PAY.

16:51.068 --> 16:52.965
-OKAY.
-AND THEN YOU'RE ALL OVER IT.

16:52.965 --> 16:54.068
Richard:
THE PLAN IS TO HAVE MY FIXER,

16:54.068 --> 16:55.689
RUSSELL,
SIT ON THE AUCTION SITE

16:55.689 --> 16:57.586
AND SEE IF WE CAN BUY
THE DARK HORSE BACK,

16:57.586 --> 16:58.896
NUMBER ONE
BECAUSE IT'S AN IMPORTANT PART

16:58.896 --> 17:00.241
OF GAS MONKEY HISTORY,

17:00.241 --> 17:03.344
AND NUMBER TWO, MAYBE I CAN
SELL IT AGAIN FOR PROFIT,

17:03.344 --> 17:06.068
AND THERE'S NOTHING LIKE MAKING
MONEY TWICE ON THE SAME CAR

17:06.068 --> 17:08.000
BECAUSE I LIKE INSTANT
PROFIT-ATION.

17:08.000 --> 17:10.172
IS THAT A REAL WORD,
PROFIT-ATION?

17:10.172 --> 17:11.689
-NO, I GUESS MADE THAT UP.
-IT'S A RICHARD-ISM.

17:11.689 --> 17:13.620
-IT'S A RICHARD-ISM.
-I KIND OF LIKE IT.

17:13.620 --> 17:15.551
-GUYS, THANK Y'ALL VERY MUCH.
-APPRECIATE YOU, BROTHER.

17:15.551 --> 17:17.206
APPRECIATE IT, MAN.
VERY GOOD TO MEET YOU.

17:17.206 --> 17:18.620
GOOD LUCK, MAN.

17:18.620 --> 17:19.862
WELL, THANKS FOR TAKING CARE
OF THE BAD GUYS FOR US, MAN.

17:19.862 --> 17:21.344
-YOU BET. TAKE CARE.
-THANK YOU, GUYS.

17:21.344 --> 17:26.103
♪♪

17:26.103 --> 17:28.586
WHAT KIND OF COMPUTER IS THIS?

17:28.586 --> 17:29.758
WE GOT THE SCOUT TO BUILD,

17:29.758 --> 17:32.034
AND RICHARD HAS GIVEN US
A VERY SHORT DEADLINE,

17:32.034 --> 17:35.758
BUT HE WANTS A LOT, WITH LOW
AND FAST BEING THE DESCRIPTION,

17:35.758 --> 17:37.103
AND HE WANTS TO USE
THE HELLCRATE,

17:37.103 --> 17:39.827
SO I'M GONNA ORDER
SOME RACE CAR PARTS.

17:39.827 --> 17:42.000
-HEY, CHRISTIE.
-WHAT, JEREMY?

17:42.000 --> 17:44.689
I NEED TO ORDER SOME PARTS,
AND RICHARD IS NOT HERE,

17:44.689 --> 17:46.965
SO I NEED A CREDIT CARD.

17:46.965 --> 17:48.655
[ BLOWS RASPBERRY ]

17:48.655 --> 17:51.206
DOES ANYBODY KNOW
YOU'RE ORDERING THEM?

17:51.206 --> 17:52.310
YEAH.

17:52.310 --> 17:53.551
I DIDN'T REALLY LIE.

17:53.551 --> 17:54.965
I MEAN, HE KNOWS WE GOT
TO ORDER PART, RIGHT?

17:54.965 --> 17:57.103
-PLEASE.
-HIGH FIVE.

17:57.103 --> 17:59.896
I CAN'T PUT THIS INTO THERE
AND GET THE PARTS.

17:59.896 --> 18:04.103
JEREMY PROMISES
THAT RICHARD KNOWS.

18:04.103 --> 18:05.620
I DON'T THINK HE DOES.

18:05.620 --> 18:08.655
YOU DIDN'T GET THE CARD FROM ME
AND I KNOW NOTHING ABOUT IT.

18:08.655 --> 18:10.137
RELUCTANTLY,
I GIVE HIM THE CARD,

18:10.137 --> 18:13.172
AND HOPEFULLY RICHARD DOES KNOW
AND I'M NOT GONNA GET FIRED.

18:13.172 --> 18:15.793
AND THAT IS HOW YOU GET
AHEAD OF THE GAME.

18:15.793 --> 18:21.103
♪♪

18:21.103 --> 18:26.310
♪♪

18:26.310 --> 18:28.482
MAN, THOSE ARE SOME
GOOD-LOOKING WHEELS.

18:28.482 --> 18:30.137
-HOW'S IT GOING, BROTHER?
-HOW'S IT GOING?

18:30.137 --> 18:31.517
-HOW'S IT GOING?
-WHAT ARE THESE FOR?

18:31.517 --> 18:33.344
THIS IS FOR THE SCOUT PROJECT
THAT RICHARD IS MAKING.

18:33.344 --> 18:34.793
-SCOUT.
-SCOUT?

18:34.793 --> 18:36.758
-YOU SURE?
-YEAH.

18:36.758 --> 18:38.448
THIS GUY, CHAD, FROM REVO
FORGED DROPPED OFF

18:38.448 --> 18:41.413
AN AMAZING SET OF BLINGED-OUT
RIMS FOR RICHARD TO SEE,

18:41.413 --> 18:42.862
AND THAT TOTALLY
CAUGHT US OFF GUARD.

18:42.862 --> 18:44.655
ME AND THE GUYS HAVE BEEN
TOTALLY UNDER THE IMPRESSION

18:44.655 --> 18:46.551
THAT WE'RE BUILDING
SOMETHING MEAN AND FAST,

18:46.551 --> 18:48.551
AND THESE WHEELS,
THEY'RE NOT REALLY LIKE THAT.

18:48.551 --> 18:50.344
PICK WHICHEVER ONE YOU
WANT AND CALL ME,

18:50.344 --> 18:51.655
AND I'LL HAVE THEM MADE UP.

18:51.655 --> 18:54.724
-OKAY.
-SEE YOU. SEE YOU LATER.

18:54.724 --> 18:56.724
DAMN, LOOK AT THOSE RIMS!

18:56.724 --> 18:58.068
I GUESS CHAD WAS JUST HERE.

18:58.068 --> 18:59.482
WHICH ONE ARE Y'ALL LIKING
FOR THE SCOUT?

18:59.482 --> 19:01.310
THIS IS NOT AT ALL WHAT WE WERE
TALKING ABOUT FOR THE SCOUT.

19:01.310 --> 19:03.344
THESE ARE DRAG STRIP
1/4-MILE RIMS.

