28:20.172 --> 28:23.241
BUT THIS IS KIND OF THE LOOK
I THINK YOU'RE GOING FOR.

28:23.241 --> 28:25.793
YEAH, ARE THESE THE EXACT
STRIPES OR DID YOU...

28:25.793 --> 28:27.000
THESE ARE THE EXACT STRIPE.

28:27.000 --> 28:28.344
NORMALLY THEY END RIGHT THERE,
THE RED --

28:28.344 --> 28:29.448
THE ORANGE STRIPES, TOO.

28:29.448 --> 28:32.310
I LIKE THE IDEA OF STILL
STOPPING SOMEWHERE

28:32.310 --> 28:34.172
IN THE GENERAL VICINITY
THAT THE ORIGINAL ONES DID.

28:34.172 --> 28:35.413
MM-HMM.

28:35.413 --> 28:37.103
BUT I WANT TO CHANGE THE STRIPES
JUST A LITTLE BIT.

28:37.103 --> 28:39.275
MAYBE THERE'S LESS OF THEM,
AND THEY'RE THICKER.

28:39.275 --> 28:40.689
THESE GUYS ARE FINALLY
STARTING TO GET WHY

28:40.689 --> 28:42.862
I'M LOWERING THE SCOUT.

28:42.862 --> 28:45.103
SOME TRUCK GUYS LIKE BIG TIRES
AND WHEELS AND LIFTS

28:45.103 --> 28:47.896
AND WHAT HAVE YOU, PRETTY MUCH
LIKE THE CAMARO WE BUILT.

28:47.896 --> 28:49.655
[ LAUGHS ]

28:49.655 --> 28:51.551
BUT THAT'S NOT BUILT FOR SPEED,
AND THE HANDLING

28:51.551 --> 28:55.206
WOULD BE ALL MESSED UP,
SO THAT'S NOT HOW I ROLL.

28:55.206 --> 28:57.758
JUST ABOUT LIKE ANY CAR I LIKE
TO DRIVE, I WANT IT DOWN LOW.

28:57.758 --> 28:59.689
THAT'S LESS DRAG,
FASTER, MEANER.

28:59.689 --> 29:00.862
THAT'S HOW WE DO IT.

29:00.862 --> 29:01.965
WHAT DO YOU THINK
ABOUT THE BUMPER

29:01.965 --> 29:03.862
AND THE LITTLE AIR-DAM SCOOP?

29:03.862 --> 29:06.206
CAN WE MAKE THIS
A FUNCTIONAL AIR INTAKE?

29:06.206 --> 29:07.620
-YES, WE CAN.
-I LIKE THAT.

29:07.620 --> 29:08.862
-PLAY WITH THE STRIPES.
-OKAY.

29:08.862 --> 29:10.862
LET'S GET RID OF
THE ORIGINAL HELLCAT LOGO

29:10.862 --> 29:12.068
BECAUSE IT'S TOO MUCH.

29:12.068 --> 29:13.034
-IT'S TOO MUCH.
-IT NEEDS TO BE SUBTLE.

29:13.034 --> 29:14.413
-OKAY.
-IT'S FRICKING RAD, DUDE.

29:14.413 --> 29:15.965
FOR A RENDERING,
IT'S PRETTY CLOSE.

29:15.965 --> 29:17.793
THIS IS ALL JUST PULLING
IMAGES AND STUFF.

29:17.793 --> 29:19.241
OH, SO IT'S LIKE CUT AND PASTE,
LIKE KINDERGARTEN.

29:19.241 --> 29:20.448
IT'S TOTALLY CUT AND PASTE.
IT'S KINDERGARTEN.

29:20.448 --> 29:21.655
OH, OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

29:21.655 --> 29:22.758
I USED PAPIER-MâCHé
WHEN YOU'RE NOT LOOKING.

29:22.758 --> 29:24.482
-WELL, GOOD JOB, GUYS.
-THANKS, BUDDY.

29:24.482 --> 29:25.827
I LOVE IT.
THROW IT TOGETHER.

29:25.827 --> 29:30.206
♪♪

29:30.206 --> 29:31.551
ALL HANDS ON SCOUT.

29:31.551 --> 29:33.034
RIGHT NOW, IT'S ALL
ABOUT THE SCOUT CHASSIS.

29:33.034 --> 29:34.310
[ WHISTLES ]

29:34.310 --> 29:35.517
WE'RE ABOUT TO START
ROCKING AND ROLLING.

29:35.517 --> 29:36.965
WE'RE GOING TO START TACKING IN,
MEASURING,

29:36.965 --> 29:38.379
AND GETTING EVERYTHING LINED UP,
BASICALLY BRING THE FRAME RAIL

29:38.379 --> 29:41.000
FROM THE BACK TO THE FRONT,
MAKE ONE BIG CHASSIS.

29:41.000 --> 29:42.034
HERE WE GO.

29:42.034 --> 29:45.344
♪♪

29:45.344 --> 29:46.724
-YOU READY?
-YEP.

29:46.724 --> 29:49.379
-WATCH YOUR BISCUITS.
-DOING A LITTLE BIT MORE.

29:49.379 --> 29:51.827
-YOU'RE DOING --
-MY BISCUITS ARE BURNING!

29:51.827 --> 29:53.448
JEREMY AND I LIVE TO FABRICATE,

29:53.448 --> 29:55.551
AND WHAT'S BETTER THAN BUILDING
A FULL FRAME FROM SCRATCH

29:55.551 --> 29:58.000
TO HANDLE 707 HORSEPOWER?

29:58.000 --> 29:59.551
WE'RE RUNNING 1x3-INCH
FRAME RAILS

29:59.551 --> 30:02.448
AND REINFORCING ALL THE SEAMS
WITH STEEL FISHPLATES.

30:02.448 --> 30:03.827
THAT'S THE PROCESS THEY USED
TO USE BACK

30:03.827 --> 30:05.655
IN THE DAY ON RAILROAD TRACKS,
SO THAT SHOULD TELL YOU

30:05.655 --> 30:08.551
HOW STRONG THIS FRAME'S
GONNA BE.

30:08.551 --> 30:11.482
-READY?
-YEP.

30:11.482 --> 30:13.206
THERE IT IS.

30:13.206 --> 30:14.655
WHEN WE'RE DONE,
WE'RE GONNA WELD THE CHASSIS

30:14.655 --> 30:16.689
TO THE SCOUT BODY,
SHEET METAL AROUND IT

30:16.689 --> 30:18.620
WHICH IS GONNA CREATE
A SUPERSTRONG CHASSIS

30:18.620 --> 30:19.620
CALLED THE UNIBODY.

30:19.620 --> 30:28.758
♪♪

30:28.758 --> 30:37.137
♪♪

30:37.137 --> 30:39.172
SO NOW THAT WE GOT THE BACK
HALF FULLY CONNECTED

30:39.172 --> 30:41.275
TO THE FRONT HALF OR FRONT
CROSSMEMBER,

30:41.275 --> 30:42.310
WE'RE MOVING FORWARD.

30:42.310 --> 30:43.482
WE CAN GET THIS THING OFF
THIS TABLE,

30:43.482 --> 30:45.206
SET THE CHASSIS BACK
UNDERNEATH THE BODY.

30:45.206 --> 30:46.344
I MEAN, EVERYTHING CAN START
HAPPENING NOW.

30:46.344 --> 30:48.310
-YOU GOT IT?
-YOU GOT A GREAT PLAN.

30:48.310 --> 30:50.103
-OH, IT'S SO LIGHT.
-OKAY, WE'RE READY.

30:50.103 --> 30:53.034
NOW WE CAN GET THE FRAME OVER TO
THE BODY AND WELD THEM TOGETHER.

30:53.034 --> 30:54.965
FORWARD, FORWARD, FORWARD!

30:54.965 --> 30:57.448
MORE FORWARD, MORE FORWARD,
MORE -- STOP.

30:57.448 --> 31:00.655
IT'S A UGLY WHEEL WELL.

31:00.655 --> 31:02.827
SO WE'RE READY TO MAKE
THIS THING A UNIBODY?

31:02.827 --> 31:04.206
YES.

31:04.206 --> 31:06.655
LET'S GET SOME WELDERS SET UP
AND MAKE TWO ONE.

31:06.655 --> 31:09.344
♪♪

31:09.344 --> 31:13.689
UNIBODY IS SHORT FOR
UNIFIED CHASSIS AND BODY.

31:13.689 --> 31:16.275
WHEN YOU MAKE THEM ONE,
IT BECOMES A UNIBODY.

31:16.275 --> 31:18.034
UP AT THE FRONT.

31:18.034 --> 31:21.620
ONCE WE LOCK IT ALL TOGETHER,
WELD IT ALL TOGETHER,

31:21.620 --> 31:23.965
IT BECOMES SUPER STRONG,
SO THAT'S WHAT WE'RE EXCITED FOR

31:23.965 --> 31:25.655
BECAUSE WE HAVE A TON
OF HORSEPOWER IN THIS THING,

31:25.655 --> 31:27.344
A LITTLE CAGE IN IT,
PROBABLY JUST THE BACK HALF.

31:27.344 --> 31:29.551
PRETTY STREETABLE VEHICLE,
SHOULD BE PRETTY SAFE.

31:29.551 --> 31:31.068
CAN'T REALLY EVEN SAY
WE HAVE A CHASSIS ANYMORE.

31:31.068 --> 31:32.758
IT'S LIKE THE CHASSIS
DISAPPEARS,

31:32.758 --> 31:34.172
AND NOW IT'S JUST A UNIBODY.

31:34.172 --> 31:36.620
IT'S LIKE, "WHERE DOES YOUR LAP
GO WHEN YOU STAND UP?"

31:36.620 --> 31:37.655
HMM.

31:37.655 --> 31:39.137
THIS IS ABSOLUTELY NOTHING

31:39.137 --> 31:41.551
THAT ANYBODY SHOULD EVER
SET OFF TO BUILD,

31:41.551 --> 31:43.862
THIS COLLABORATION OF PARTS
AND VEHICLE AND, LIKE...

31:43.862 --> 31:44.862
I'M ENJOYING IT.

31:44.862 --> 31:47.551
IT'S A COOL FRANKENSTEIN BUILD.

31:47.551 --> 31:48.896
I THINK ON SOMETHING LIKE THAT,
THOUGH,

31:48.896 --> 31:50.448
AS LONG AS YOU STAY CLEAN

31:50.448 --> 31:53.413
BECAUSE WHEN IT GETS WEIRD IS
WHEN YOU'RE LIKE, "OH, [BLEEP]."

31:53.413 --> 31:55.137
IT NEEDS TO BE
A CERTAIN THEME, TOO.

31:55.137 --> 31:56.448
LIKE, I KNOW THAT WE GOT
EVERYTHING EVERYWHERE,

31:56.448 --> 31:57.862
BUT IF WE CAN STAY IN A THEME,

31:57.862 --> 31:59.344
YOU KNOW, AMONGST EACH OTHER,
THEN IT STAYS COOL.

31:59.344 --> 32:01.172
THE THEME IS CLEAN.

32:01.172 --> 32:03.551
-OOH, I LIKE THAT.
-THE THEME IS CLEAN.

32:03.551 --> 32:04.586
-GOT IT.
-WHAT'S UP?

32:04.586 --> 32:05.827
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

32:05.827 --> 32:07.137
-IT'S WORKING.
-HEY, HEY.

32:07.137 --> 32:09.793
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF YOUR NOW-UNIBODY SCOUT?

32:09.793 --> 32:13.448
LET ME SEE THIS.

32:13.448 --> 32:14.862
FRICKING RAD.

32:14.862 --> 32:16.379
I KEEP CHECKING ON THESE GUYS
BECAUSE I'M NOT SURE

32:16.379 --> 32:18.827
THAT THEY GET WHERE I'M TRYING
TO GO WITH THE SCOUT BUILD.

32:18.827 --> 32:20.965
ALL RIGHT.
SO IF WE'RE UNIBODY NOW,

32:20.965 --> 32:22.931
WHAT DID WE PUT UNDER THIS,
OR IS THAT IT?

32:22.931 --> 32:24.137
-THAT'S IT.
-SO WE'RE...

32:24.137 --> 32:25.517
TWO FRAME RAILS
RUN ALL THE WAY FORWARD

32:25.517 --> 32:27.413
ON THIS THING UP
TO THE FRONT CROSSMEMBER.

32:27.413 --> 32:29.827
-WHERE DO THEY MEET?
-RIGHT UP TO THIS.

32:29.827 --> 32:31.241
YEAH, SO THIS REPLACES
THAT BIG FACTORY

32:31.241 --> 32:32.620
CROSSMEMBER THAT WAS HERE.

32:32.620 --> 32:34.655
THAT'S WHY WE PLATED THIS ALL IN
AND ADDED THESE GUSSETS.

32:34.655 --> 32:36.034
ALL RIGHT.

32:36.034 --> 32:37.620
SO IS THE METALWORK DONE,
BODY READY TO BE PAINTED?

32:37.620 --> 32:39.241
-YEAH.
-NOT EVEN CLOSE.

32:39.241 --> 32:40.862
THIS IS WEEK ONE?

32:40.862 --> 32:42.034
-YEAH.
-YES.

32:42.034 --> 32:43.551
YOU'RE ONLY IN WEEK ONE,
SO WE'VE DONE A LOT.

32:43.551 --> 32:45.827
THIS WAS A RUNNING,
DRIVING VEHICLE WHEN IT CAME IN.

32:45.827 --> 32:47.344
WELL, YEAH, AND LOOK
WHAT YOU DID TO IT.

32:47.344 --> 32:48.689
NOW IT DOESN'T EVEN RUN
OR DRIVE.

32:48.689 --> 32:50.517
I HATE TO BREAK IT TO YOU,
BUT WE'RE STILL MISSING

32:50.517 --> 32:51.862
A BIG CHUNK OF THE DRIVETRAIN.

32:51.862 --> 32:53.275
WE'RE HAVING A LOT OF TROUBLE,

32:53.275 --> 32:54.793
MAYBE YOU CAN CALL IN A FAVOR
TO YOUR DODGE GUYS,

32:54.793 --> 32:57.206
GETTING OUR EIGHT-SPEED
AUTOMATIC THAT YOU WANT.

32:57.206 --> 32:58.655
WHY?

32:58.655 --> 32:59.655
WE'VE -- IT'S JUST --
THEY JUST DON'T HAVE THEM.

32:59.655 --> 33:00.655
IT'S JUST DELAYED.
NOBODY HAS THEM.

33:00.655 --> 33:02.068
I MEAN, THEY'RE HARD TO GET.

33:02.068 --> 33:03.241
AND IF THEY HAVE THEM,
THEY'RE PUTTING THEM IN ONE

33:03.241 --> 33:04.517
THAT THEY MIGHT BE
REPAIRING FOR SOME REASON.

33:04.517 --> 33:06.103
-YEAH.
-IT'S NOT MY PROBLEM.

33:06.103 --> 33:07.896
I MEAN, WHEN Y'ALL START
BITCHING WHEN I'M TRYING

33:07.896 --> 33:09.793
TO GIVE YOU COMPLIMENTS
IS WHEN IT'S MY EXIT.

33:09.793 --> 33:11.620
[ LAUGHTER ]

33:11.620 --> 33:14.000
BECAUSE IT IS, LIKE, LATE,
LATE FRIDAY NIGHT RIGHT NOW.

33:14.000 --> 33:16.448
HEY, DO YOU SEE HOW DARK IT
IS OUTSIDE?

33:16.448 --> 33:17.517
-YEAH, AND WE'RE STILL HERE.
-YOU GOT US HERE ALL NIGHT.

33:17.517 --> 33:20.655
-YEAH.
-IT'S ONLY 5:00!

33:20.655 --> 33:22.379
IT JUST GETS DARK EARLY!

33:22.379 --> 33:26.206
♪♪

33:26.206 --> 33:27.620
WHOO!

33:27.620 --> 33:28.793
Narrator:
COMING UP ON "FAST N' LOUD,"

33:28.793 --> 33:30.275
THE MONKEYS POWER UP.

33:30.275 --> 33:31.275
WHOO-HOO-HOO-HOO-HOO!

33:31.275 --> 33:33.413
-WE HAVE A MOTOR.
-THAT'S NICE.

33:33.413 --> 33:36.034
Narrator: BUT PROBLEMS MIGHT
SHUT THEM DOWN.

33:36.034 --> 33:37.137
I DON'T THINK
THIS IS GONNA WORK, DUDE.

33:37.137 --> 33:39.344
Narrator:
AND RICHARD PLAYS MATCHMAKER.

33:39.344 --> 33:41.448
I HAVE BEEN LOOKING FOR
THIS TRUCK ABOUT 8, 10 YEARS.

33:41.448 --> 33:42.655
[ LAUGHS ]

33:42.655 --> 33:45.103
OH, IT'S THERE, MAN.

33:46.965 --> 33:51.413
♪♪

33:51.413 --> 33:53.275
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN HERE?
-HI, RICHARD.

33:53.275 --> 33:55.000
WHO LET YOU --
DAPHNE, YOU LET HER IN HERE?

33:55.000 --> 33:56.586
THEY SAY RICHARD
IS SCARED OF ME.

33:56.586 --> 33:59.172
I'M GONNA TRY
TO MAKE UP WITH HIM.

33:59.172 --> 34:01.344
WHAT IS THIS?
IS IT ALIVE?

34:01.344 --> 34:04.137
OH, THAT'S GOOD, AND IT'S COLD,
AND A TACO?

34:04.137 --> 34:06.275
-YES. WHAT DO YOU THINK OF --
-CHICKEN TACO?

34:06.275 --> 34:07.724
-WHOO!
-WHAT DO YOU WANT?

34:07.724 --> 34:12.000
SO WHAT I WANT, WHEN ARE YOU
GONNA GIVE ME THE BUSINESS?

34:12.000 --> 34:13.758
THAT'S PRETTY MUCH ALL I EVER DO
IS GIVE YOU THE BUSINESS.

34:13.758 --> 34:15.034
OH, COME ON.

34:15.034 --> 34:16.931
OKAY, I'LL TRY TO FIND
SOME BUSINESS FOR YOU.

34:16.931 --> 34:17.965
-OKAY.
-I CAN'T GUARANTEE IT.

34:17.965 --> 34:19.103
-YOU PROMISE?
-I PROMISE.

34:19.103 --> 34:20.517
YOU PROMISE!

34:20.517 --> 34:22.482
HEY, LOW TONES.

34:22.482 --> 34:23.517
OKAY.

34:23.517 --> 34:26.034
YOU WERE NICE FOR, LIKE,
32 SECONDS.

34:26.034 --> 34:28.172
PROBABLY POISONED THE TACO, TOO.
I AIN'T EATING THAT [BLEEP].

34:28.172 --> 34:29.482
I'LL TAKE THE BEER, THOUGH.

34:29.482 --> 34:30.758
ASS MONKEY, AS USUAL.

34:32.655 --> 34:34.862
♪♪

34:34.862 --> 34:36.172
Richard: WE HAD SOME WEATHER
ROLL IN THIS MORNING,

34:36.172 --> 34:38.620
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY
ABOUT RAINY DAYS.

34:38.620 --> 34:43.758
THEY'RE PERFECT FOR UNLOADING
WEIRD-ASS TRUCKS.

34:43.758 --> 34:46.068
A WHILE BACK, WE FOUND A VERY,
VERY CUSTOM TRUCK

34:46.068 --> 34:48.620
THAT WAS EXTREMELY POPULAR
WITH THE TRUCKING CROWD

34:48.620 --> 34:51.620
AND RESURRECTED IT,
IF YOU WILL.

34:51.620 --> 34:53.103
BUT SINCE THEN, IT'S BEEN
TAKING UP SPACE,

34:53.103 --> 34:55.172
AND, TO BE HONEST,
NO ONE'S LINING UP TO BUY IT.

34:55.172 --> 34:57.379
[ SWITCH CLICKS ]

34:57.379 --> 34:59.344
HOPEFULLY THAT'LL CHANGE TODAY.

34:59.344 --> 35:00.655
DAVID,
YOU PICKED A PERFECT DAY

35:00.655 --> 35:05.034
TO LOOK AT A SIX-PERSON
CONVERTIBLE DUALLY.

35:05.034 --> 35:07.137
YEAH, THIS RAIN WASN'T KIND OF
IN THE PLAN.

35:07.137 --> 35:09.517
MY NAME IS DAVID SHULMAN.
I'M FROM ORLANDO, FLORIDA,

35:09.517 --> 35:12.137
AND THIS IS MY BUDDY,
BRIAN RODRIGUEZ, FROM ATLANTA.

35:12.137 --> 35:14.379
Richard: WELL, THERE SHE IS,
MAN, THE KREW KUT DUALLY

35:14.379 --> 35:17.413
THAT EVERY ONE OF US HAVE KNOWN
FOR MANY, MANY YEARS.

35:17.413 --> 35:20.413
YEAH, THIS THING LOOKS AS GOOD
AS IT DID PROBABLY,

35:20.413 --> 35:23.172
LIKE, 18, 20 YEARS AGO.
-OH, FOR SURE.

35:23.172 --> 35:24.172
I MEAN, THIS IS ALL
THE ORIGINAL PAINT.

35:24.172 --> 35:25.724
WE TOUCHED UP
A COUPLE OF SPOTS.

35:25.724 --> 35:27.724
WE WERE THINKING ABOUT
PUTTING OUR OWN SPIN ON IT,

35:27.724 --> 35:29.379
AND THEN WE WERE LIKE,
"NO. LET'S JUST MAKE IT

35:29.379 --> 35:31.379
WHAT IT WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
IN THE FIRST PLACE."

35:31.379 --> 35:33.896
I HAD BEEN LOOKING FOR THIS
TRUCK, LIKE, FOR YEARS

35:33.896 --> 35:35.448
AND YEARS,
ABOUT 8, 10 YEARS.

35:35.448 --> 35:37.310
-I TRIED TO BUY IT.
-WHAT DO YOU GOT HERE?

35:37.310 --> 35:39.862
WELL, THIS IS SOME PICTURES
BACK IN THE DAY

35:39.862 --> 35:41.241
WHEN I WENT OUT
TO CALIFORNIA.

35:41.241 --> 35:42.551
I USED TO FLY OUT FOR

35:42.551 --> 35:44.413
THE CALIFORNIA TRUCK
JAMBOREE SHOW

35:44.413 --> 35:46.965
AND WENT TO MIC AND SAT IN IT,

35:46.965 --> 35:49.827
AND, I MEAN,
THAT WAS 20 YEARS AGO.

35:49.827 --> 35:50.931
HECK YEAH.

35:50.931 --> 35:52.344
Richard:
HE'S KIND OF CHASED THIS TRUCK,

35:52.344 --> 35:54.689
AND I KIND OF SNUCK IT OUT
FROM UNDER HIM WHEN I FOUND IT

35:54.689 --> 35:57.034
AND SCOOPED IT UP FOR $7,500.

35:57.034 --> 35:58.655
ALL RIGHT, $7,500.

35:58.655 --> 36:00.137
-Y'ALL BRING US SOME --
-ALL RIGHT.

36:00.137 --> 36:01.793
BUT THAT WAS JUST THE START
BECAUSE I'VE PUT IN AT LEAST

36:01.793 --> 36:03.965
ANOTHER 40 GRAND,
AND IT'S BADASS,

36:03.965 --> 36:05.965
AND SO IT'S 10 TIMES THE TRUCK
HE WOULD HAVE GOTTEN,

36:05.965 --> 36:08.172
AND IT'S PROBABLY GONNA BE
10 TIMES THE MONEY.

36:08.172 --> 36:10.068
I THINK I MAY GET A LITTLE BIT
WET DRIVING THIS THING.

36:10.068 --> 36:12.034
I GOT A TRUCK SHOW
TO GO TO, SO...

36:12.034 --> 36:14.000
YOU MEAN IF YOU BUY IT, YOU'RE
GOING TO DRIVE IT IN THIS?

36:14.000 --> 36:16.344
YEAH!
WHY ELSE DO YOU BUY A CAR?

36:16.344 --> 36:17.689
DON'T THINK I'M GONNA
TAKE PITY ON YOU

36:17.689 --> 36:18.862
AND GIVE YOU A DISCOUNT
BECAUSE YOU'RE CRAZY ENOUGH

36:18.862 --> 36:20.448
TO DRIVE IT IN THE RAIN.
-OH, COME ON.

36:20.448 --> 36:22.000
[ LAUGHS ]

36:22.000 --> 36:23.241
IT'S GONNA RAIN,

36:23.241 --> 36:25.379
AND THIS THING HAS NO TOP,
AND ON TOP OF THAT,

36:25.379 --> 36:27.620
IT DOESN'T HAVE
WINDSHIELD WIPERS, NEVER HAS.

36:27.620 --> 36:30.896
THIS THING HAD THAT BOAT
ANCHOR OF A 454 MOTOR IN IT,

36:30.896 --> 36:32.724
SO WE STEPPED IT UP
A LITTLE BIT.

36:32.724 --> 36:36.896
THAT'S A K-TEC ONE-OFF BUILD LSX
WITH ABOUT 600-PLUS HORSEPOWER.

36:36.896 --> 36:42.068
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

36:42.068 --> 36:43.103
THAT'S GONNA GET IT.

36:43.103 --> 36:48.965
THAT IS GONNA BE
A LOT OF FUN.

36:48.965 --> 36:51.275
SO WITH THE ACCUAIR SYSTEM
WORKING THE HYDRAULICS,

36:51.275 --> 36:54.793
IT'S NOT LIKE SWITCHES,
SO IT'S JUST EASY UP AND DOWN.

36:54.793 --> 36:56.931
I BET YOU FELLAS CAN'T WAIT
TO GO FOR A RIDE.

36:56.931 --> 36:59.482
IT'S NOT RAINING TOO BAD.
IT'S KIND OF UP TO YOU.

36:59.482 --> 37:02.103
YEAH, IT'S NOT BAD.
I'LL GO FOR A RIDE.

37:02.103 --> 37:03.586
LET'S DO IT.

37:03.586 --> 37:07.586
♪♪

37:07.586 --> 37:09.448
SOUNDS AWESOME.

37:09.448 --> 37:12.931
OH, IT'S RAD.

37:12.931 --> 37:14.172
DAMN.

37:14.172 --> 37:15.310
[ HORN HONKS ]

37:15.310 --> 37:16.413
THEY LIKE IT.

37:16.413 --> 37:18.379
THIS THING DEFINITELY
GETS ATTENTION.

37:18.379 --> 37:19.793
WELL, WE'RE PROBABLY THE ONLY
GUYS IN A DUALLY

37:19.793 --> 37:21.620
CONVERTIBLE IN THE RAIN.

37:21.620 --> 37:23.482
[ LAUGHS ]

37:23.482 --> 37:28.931
♪♪

37:28.931 --> 37:30.586
-IT'LL GET IT.
-OH, IT'S THERE, MAN.

37:30.586 --> 37:33.137
[ LAUGHTER ]

37:33.137 --> 37:36.551
LOOK AT THAT. WE MADE IT
WITHOUT GETTING RAINED ON.

37:36.551 --> 37:38.551
NOW, IF I COULD ONLY MAKE IT
TO THE SHOW LIKE THAT.

37:38.551 --> 37:40.172
WELL, YOU GOT TO MAKE
A DEAL FIRST.

37:40.172 --> 37:43.206
AS FAR AS FAIR MONEY,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT SHOULD BE.

37:43.206 --> 37:47.241
I MEAN, YOU GOT A SIX-SEATER,
FOUR-DOOR CREW CAB LONG-BED

37:47.241 --> 37:50.241
DUALLY ONE-TON.

37:50.241 --> 37:51.758
I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S NOT IN THE BOOK.

37:51.758 --> 37:53.310
I CAN'T PRICE IT.

37:53.310 --> 37:54.793
WELL, I'M THINKING THAT
IT SHOULD BE WORTH

37:54.793 --> 37:58.482
AROUND 55 TO 60,

37:58.482 --> 38:00.758
SO HOW ABOUT 55 GRAND?

38:00.758 --> 38:03.793
I WAS THINKING MORE LIKE
IN THE 40 RANGE.

38:03.793 --> 38:06.137
NO. I CAN GET 40 FOR IT
ALL DAY LONG,

38:06.137 --> 38:07.896
BUT, YOU KNOW,
I'M HERE TO SELL IT.

38:07.896 --> 38:10.758
IT TAKES UP A LOT OF SPACE HERE,
SO I DON'T KNOW.

38:10.758 --> 38:12.724
HOW ABOUT 50?

38:12.724 --> 38:14.586
I KNOW I CAN'T BUILD IT
ANYWHERE NEAR THAT.

38:14.586 --> 38:16.517
NO WAY.

38:16.517 --> 38:17.655
ALL RIGHT, I'LL DO 50.

38:17.655 --> 38:19.620
KILLER, RIGHT ON, MAN.

38:19.620 --> 38:21.068
GOOD JOB, GUYS.

38:21.068 --> 38:23.344
SO I HIT HIM WITH AROUND 60
JUST TO SEE WHERE HE WAS AT.

38:23.344 --> 38:24.931
WE SETTLED ON 50 GRAND.

38:24.931 --> 38:26.413
I THINK THAT'S ALL OF IT.

38:26.413 --> 38:28.517
I DON'T THINK I COULD HAVE GOT
ANY BETTER AT AN AUCTION,

38:28.517 --> 38:30.551
AND I THINK HE WAS THE BUYER.

38:30.551 --> 38:32.724
AS THEY SAY, THERE'S AN ASS
FOR EVERY SEAT.

38:32.724 --> 38:34.448
DAVID IS THAT ASS TODAY.

38:34.448 --> 38:36.448
LET'S GO DO SOME PAPERWORK,
AND THEN YOU'RE REALLY GOING

38:36.448 --> 38:38.344
TO JUMP IN IT RIGHT NOW
AND GO TO MISSISSIPPI?

38:38.344 --> 38:40.137
YEAH.
WHY DO YOU THINK I BOUGHT IT?

38:40.137 --> 38:41.448
THAT IS SO BADASS.

38:41.448 --> 38:42.724
I WISH I HAD TIME
TO DO COOL THINGS.

38:42.724 --> 38:50.448
♪♪

38:50.448 --> 38:52.896
MAYBE I SHOULDN'T SIT ON IT.
IT SAYS, "DO NOT STACK."

38:52.896 --> 38:55.137
IF MY MOM SAW THIS,
I WOULD BE DEAD.

38:55.137 --> 38:57.103
HEY, IF YOUR MOM SAW THIS,
I'D BE DEAD.

38:57.103 --> 39:00.137
I AIN'T GOT NO HANDS ON IT.
WHOA!

39:00.137 --> 39:02.068
FOUND THE KEY.

39:02.068 --> 39:04.758
WE'RE A LITTLE OVER A WEEK
INTO THE BUILD ON THE '79 SCOUT,

39:04.758 --> 39:07.137
AND RIGHT NOW WE'RE TAKING
A 707-HORSEPOWER

39:07.137 --> 39:08.689
HELLCRATE MOTOR OFF THE SHELF

39:08.689 --> 39:09.931
BECAUSE RICHARD PULLED
SOME STRINGS

39:09.931 --> 39:11.931
TO GET THE EIGHT-SPEED TRANNY.

39:11.931 --> 39:13.413
NOW WE CAN FINALLY MARRY
THE TWO TOGETHER

39:13.413 --> 39:16.655
AND DO A MOCK STUB
OF THE DRIVETRAIN.

39:16.655 --> 39:19.137
-LET'S DO THIS.
-GET YOU SOME OF THAT.

39:19.137 --> 39:21.034
THE HELLCRATE, IT'S A BIG DEAL.

39:21.034 --> 39:22.241
IS THIS THE END
THAT THIS POPS OUT?

39:22.241 --> 39:23.310
WHOO-HOO-HOO-HOO-HOO!

39:23.310 --> 39:24.620
-WE HAVE A MOTOR!
-DUDE.

39:24.620 --> 39:26.206
-THAT'S NICE.
-IT TOOK UP THE WHOLE CRATE.

39:26.206 --> 39:28.034
-LOT OF POWER.
-OH, MAN.

39:28.034 --> 39:30.034
THE HELLCRATE IS THE SAME MOTOR
AS THE HELLCAT,

39:30.034 --> 39:31.689
WHICH YOU'LL FIND
IN THE DODGE CHARGER.

39:31.689 --> 39:33.137
ONLY THING IS, THIS BABY
IS MEANT TO BE

39:33.137 --> 39:34.758
RETROFITTED INTO OTHER CARS.

39:34.758 --> 39:36.000
I'M WAITING ON A TRANS.

39:36.000 --> 39:37.724
TRANS GOT HERE THIS MORNING,
SO THAT'S HERE.

39:37.724 --> 39:39.068
-WHERE'S IT AT?
-SWEET.

39:39.068 --> 39:40.965
WELL, THEN I CAN BOLT THE MOTOR
AND TRANS TOGETHER,

39:40.965 --> 39:42.034
AND WHILE YOU GUYS ARE
FINISHING UP THE METALWORKING,

39:42.034 --> 39:43.137
YOU'RE FINISHING UP
YOUR BRACKETS,

39:43.137 --> 39:44.310
WE CAN DROP THAT THING IN.

39:44.310 --> 39:45.586
YEAH, DROP IT IN,
SEE IF IT CLEARS THE FLOOR.

39:45.586 --> 39:46.620
-THAT'D BE AWESOME.
-I'LL SET ALL THEM OUT HERE.

39:46.620 --> 39:48.172
YEAH.

39:48.172 --> 39:50.586
IT'S THE FIRST SUPERCHARGED
FACTORY-DIRECT 707-HORSEPOWER

39:50.586 --> 39:52.448
CRATE ENGINE KIT EVER SOLD.

39:52.448 --> 39:53.965
EVEN COOLER IS
WE'RE GONNA TO BE THE FIRST

39:53.965 --> 39:56.827
TO EVER PUT ONE INTO A SCOUT.

39:56.827 --> 39:58.241
THIS THING WEIGHS A TON.

39:58.241 --> 40:00.103
WE'RE USING AN EIGHT-SPEED
AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION

40:00.103 --> 40:02.103
FROM MOPAR.
IT COMES WITH A TORQUE CONVERTER

40:02.103 --> 40:04.206
FOR LIGHTNING-FAST SHIFTS
AND ACCELERATION.

40:04.206 --> 40:05.931
WE WANT TO DROP IN THE MOTOR
AND TRANSMISSION

40:05.931 --> 40:07.206
TO DO A MOCK-UP
OF HOW IT'S GONNA

40:07.206 --> 40:08.931
SIT INSIDE THE ENGINE BAY

40:08.931 --> 40:10.448
SO WE CAN SEE WHERE WE WANT
TO BUILD OUR MOTOR

40:10.448 --> 40:14.275
AND TRANSMISSION MOUNTS
BEFORE IT ALL GOES OFF TO PAINT.

40:14.275 --> 40:18.448
LOOKING AT THAT, PAN,
THIS CROSSMEMBER.

40:18.448 --> 40:20.965
YEAH, IS THAT MOTOR BACKWARDS
RIGHT NOW?

40:20.965 --> 40:23.793
-HEY, JASON.
-SIR.

40:23.793 --> 40:25.965
NOW THAT WE GOT THE MOTOR ON,
CAN REALLY LOOK AT IT,

40:25.965 --> 40:28.000
AND THE CROSSMEMBER THAT WE HAVE
WITH THE RACK AND PINION

40:28.000 --> 40:29.517
AND EVERYTHING --
-YEAH.

40:29.517 --> 40:32.344
THIS FRONT SUMP PAN
IS NOT GOING TO CLEAR.

40:32.344 --> 40:33.517
-YEAH.
-IT'S NOT GONNA CLEAR.

40:33.517 --> 40:34.517
IT'LL PUT OUR MOTOR
RIGHT THROUGH THE HOOD.

40:34.517 --> 40:35.793
OUR DRIVESHAFT WOULD BE
TOO HIGH.

40:35.793 --> 40:38.827
IT WOULD JUST CREATE
TOO MANY PROBLEMS DOWN THE ROAD.

40:38.827 --> 40:40.655
-THAT IS A PRETTY TALL SUMP.
-YEAH.

40:40.655 --> 40:42.620
WHAT IS IT, LIKE,
6 INCHES TALL?

40:42.620 --> 40:44.379
SO THAT DOES MAKE A LOT OF
DIFFERENCE ON A STEERING RACK.

40:44.379 --> 40:45.793
I DON'T THINK THIS IS
GONNA WORK, DUDE.

40:45.793 --> 40:46.965
WE SHOULD HAVE HAD THE MOTOR
AND TRANSMISSION

40:46.965 --> 40:49.103
IN DAYS AGO, LIKE, DAYS AGO.

40:49.103 --> 40:50.827
WE'RE STARTING TO FEEL
THE STRESS A LITTLE BIT.

40:50.827 --> 40:52.724
IT'S GONNA STINK.

40:52.724 --> 40:54.689
Narrator:
NEXT WEEK ON "FAST N' LOUD"...

40:54.689 --> 40:56.137
YOU'RE LOSING YOUR ASS
BACK THERE.

40:56.137 --> 40:59.172
Narrator: THE MONKEYS RACE TO
FINISH THE SCOUT FROM HELL,

40:59.172 --> 41:02.068
BUT BEING THE FIRST TO PUT
A HELLCRATE ENGINE IN A SCOUT

41:02.068 --> 41:03.655
IS MORE THAN THEY BARGAINED FOR.

41:03.655 --> 41:05.275
ISN'T THIS WHAT
YOU PLANNED IT TO BE?

41:05.275 --> 41:06.827
I DON'T THINK I WANT
BLACK LEATHER.

41:06.827 --> 41:08.344
Narrator:
AND RICHARD'S INTERIOR DESIGN

41:08.344 --> 41:11.241
MIGHT TURN HEADS AND STOMACHS

41:11.241 --> 41:14.551
UNTIL RICHARD FINDS HIMSELF
DEALING WITH AN OLD NEMESIS.

41:14.551 --> 41:15.758
HEY, ASS MONKEY!

41:15.758 --> 41:17.413
YOU GOT TO COME UP
WITH A NEW CATCHPHRASE.

41:17.413 --> 41:20.275
Narrator: PLUS, RICHARD GOES TO
SEE DENNIS FOR A SHOPPING SPREE

41:20.275 --> 41:23.655
AND COMES HOME
WITH A 1963 SPLIT-WINDOW.

41:23.655 --> 41:24.931
Richard:
THIS IS A COOL-ASS CAR.

41:24.931 --> 41:27.275
Narrator: CAN THE MONKEYS
FULFILL RICHARD'S VISION,

41:27.275 --> 41:30.482
OR WILL HE END UP WITH
A SUPERPOWERED ORANGE CRATE?

41:30.482 --> 41:32.275
WE GOT A PROBLEM.

41:32.275 --> 41:33.379
THAT DOESN'T LOOK GOOD.
